The set-up of the workshop is designed as an assessment center. Please prepare for the session as if you were attending an assessment center for an internship or graduate job and bring along a job/ internship description that is of interest to you (in printed version). 

What you should expect from of the workshop is to: 
• discover the structure of and meaning behind the exercises in an AC; 
• discover how to practice for ACs; 
• develop your interview skills; 
• discover what employers look at during an AC process; 
• discover how you interact with the 'competition' (the other students) in such a setting; 
• find out about interviewing techniques and games the employer might surprise you with; 
• discover the influence of your behavior and results on getting hired 
• acknowledge what you should work on so that the real interview is a success! 

The session will consist of the following: 
• introduction to assessment centers, their processes and tips; 
• a mock assessment center; 
• feedback.
